    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To track down memory leaks, you'll need profiling tools, as the culprit is often hidden within the code's object graph. Tools like `memory_profiler` are excellent for line-by-line memory tracking of Python code. For deeper, more complex issues, you can use `tracemalloc`, which records memory blocks allocated by Python and lets you inspect the traceback of where those allocations occurred. These tools help make the invisible memory usage visible to you.",
      "source": "target",
